Add implementations: ducks-reducer & middleware (#71)

Add ducks-reducer and ducks-middleware that are tools that assumes that ducks are combined in a single object and then you can use them all to create the store.

```javascript
import ducksReducer from 'ducks-reducer'
import ducksMiddleware from 'ducks-middleware'

import * as duckWishes from 'duck-wishes'
import * as comments from './comments'
import * as posts from './posts'
import * as users from './users'

const ducks = { comments, posts, users, duckWishes }
const reducer = ducksReducer(ducks)
const middleware = ducksMiddleware(ducks)

const store = createStore(
  reducer, 
  preloadedState, 
  applyMiddleware(middleware)
)
```

Clarify what happens when importing * (#67)

* Clarify what happens when importing *

I think that mentioning what happens is enough, given that it works even with `default` there.

It only adds an extra action named `default` that won't work... but I don't think it is really a problem.
